In this paper a search for direct pair production of the top squark is reported, in final states with two isolated leptons (electrons or muons) and missing transverse momentum. The search utilises 36.1fb-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$36.1~\hbox {fb}^{-1}$$\end{document} of proton–proton collision data collected by the ATLAS experiment in 2015 and 2016 at a centre-of-mass energy s=13\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sqrt{s}=13$$\end{document} TeV.

