Table 10 shows the expected and observed numbers of events in each of the control regions after the background fit. The total number of fitted background events in the validation regions is in agreement with the observed number of data events. Figure 3 shows three distributions in the control regions after the background fit, so that the plots illustrate the MC modelling of the shape of each variable. In general, good agreement between the data and the background model is found within uncertainties. The other selection variables are equally well described by the background prediction. Good agreement, within one standard deviation from the SM background prediction, is observed in the VRs and summarised in Fig. 5.Table 10
