				\begin{document}$$t\bar{t}$$\end{document} and the multi-jet parameterisation is assigned as the systematic uncertainty in the central FNP prediction and symmetrised.

Table 13 summarises the contributions of the different sources of systematic uncertainty in the total SM background predictions in the signal regions. The total systematic uncertainty ranges between 15% and 46%, with the dominant sources being the size of the MC event samples, the JES and ETmiss\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
